Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

This change needed to be refactored to do the full conversion of data, as alex noted.

However, on further consideration and with the help of http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-March/030404.html it seemed that this conversion needs to be an out-of-band step for the migrations.

The current approach follows:
1) add a deprecated option to skip the utf8 sanity check
    - the option will be anticipated to be removed in juno
2) expect that deployers will perform the charset migration out-of-band of glance db migrations
    - the hope is that we can upstream a tool to perform the necessary checking to prevent corruption and ease the burden of such a large data operation
Patch Set 7: Abandoned
